{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PsXnAhy3LrdtD8RUc5kukG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23\n     2→\n     3→### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — verify (2026-03-23T05:45Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\n     6→- **Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running (using `codeharness-shared-*` naming). The `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts. Worked around by using the shared stack directly.\n     7→- **Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path.\n     8→- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find story Status line in the story file — likely looking for `## Status:` pattern that was stripped or mismatched.\n     9→\n    10→### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — create-story (2026-03-23T05:55Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\n    13→- **File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\n    14→- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n    15→\n    16→### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)\n    17→\n    18→- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\n    19→- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\n    20→- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\n    21→\n    22→### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — code-review (2026-03-23T06:07Z)\n    23→\n    24→- **HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\n    25→- **LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` — if tarpaulin outputs `\"coverage\": \"85.5\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\n    26→- **LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\n    27→- **Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n    28→- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\n    29→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"068788d2-fa6f-4c6d-aa64-12d986e1d458","uuid":"365831f4-f96d-489b-b9d7-2439aab66fac","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:11:06.882Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23\n\n### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — verify (2026-03-23T05:45Z)\n\n- **Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\n- **Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running (using `codeharness-shared-*` naming). The `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts. Worked around by using the shared stack directly.\n- **Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path.\n- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find story Status line in the story file — likely looking for `## Status:` pattern that was stripped or mismatched.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — create-story (2026-03-23T05:55Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\n- **File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\n- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)\n\n- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\n- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\n- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — code-review (2026-03-23T06:07Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\n- **LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` — if tarpaulin outputs `\"coverage\": \"85.5\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\n- **LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\n- **Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\n","numLines":29,"startLine":1,"totalLines":29}}}
