{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XeC36MVpdZBeu6ZuZmekUQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8.3: cargo-tarpaulin coverage detection and parsing\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer running coverage on a Rust project,\n     8→I want codeharness to detect cargo-tarpaulin, run it, and parse the JSON report,\n     9→so that coverage metrics are tracked at parity with Node.js/Python.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [x] AC1: Given a Rust project with `cargo-tarpaulin` installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'cargo-tarpaulin', runCommand: 'cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/', reportFormat: 'tarpaulin-json' }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [x] AC2: Given a Rust workspace project (Cargo.toml contains `[workspace]`), when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then the run command includes `--workspace` flag <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC3: Given a `coverage/tarpaulin-report.json` file with `\"coverage\": 85.5`, when `parseCoverageReport()` is called with format `'tarpaulin-json'`, then it returns `85.5` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC4: Given `cargo test` output containing `test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored`, when `parseTestCounts()` is called, then it returns `{ passCount: 42, failCount: 3 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [x] AC5: Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is NOT installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called on a Rust project, then it returns `{ tool: 'unknown' }` with a warning <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→\n    19→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    20→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"068788d2-fa6f-4c6d-aa64-12d986e1d458","uuid":"66d08359-56fd-48f9-bc0a-2bdcaaa93a4e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:12:01.724Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/codeharness-verify-8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection/story.md","content":"# Story 8.3: cargo-tarpaulin coverage detection and parsing\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer running coverage on a Rust project,\nI want codeharness to detect cargo-tarpaulin, run it, and parse the JSON report,\nso that coverage metrics are tracked at parity with Node.js/Python.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [x] AC1: Given a Rust project with `cargo-tarpaulin` installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'cargo-tarpaulin', runCommand: 'cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/', reportFormat: 'tarpaulin-json' }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [x] AC2: Given a Rust workspace project (Cargo.toml contains `[workspace]`), when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then the run command includes `--workspace` flag <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [x] AC3: Given a `coverage/tarpaulin-report.json` file with `\"coverage\": 85.5`, when `parseCoverageReport()` is called with format `'tarpaulin-json'`, then it returns `85.5` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [x] AC4: Given `cargo test` output containing `test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored`, when `parseTestCounts()` is called, then it returns `{ passCount: 42, failCount: 3 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [x] AC5: Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is NOT installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called on a Rust project, then it returns `{ tool: 'unknown' }` with a warning <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n","numLines":20,"startLine":1,"totalLines":271}}}
