{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XFnAENTyq274MDpTvHybLC","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"068788d2-fa6f-4c6d-aa64-12d986e1d458","uuid":"46ae7eb5-4c18-4ce5-a104-30f52628fb8d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:17:51.270Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.","newString":"- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — verify (2026-03-23T10:17Z)\n\n- **CLI does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` in JSON output.** `codeharness coverage --json` output includes `tool` but not other `detectCoverageTool()` fields. AC1 and AC2 required supplemental verification by replicating function logic from `dist/index.js`. Documentation/API gap.\n- **AC4 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `parseTestCounts` is internal and not exercised by any CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output. No `codeharness parse-test-output` command.\n- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** No log entries in VictoriaLogs during verification. Expected — container doesn't have Docker-in-Docker so observability stack not running inside it.\n- **Workspace aggregation confirmed.** Bundle shows `parseTestCounts` uses global regex with `matchAll`-style loop for multi-crate workspace test output.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23\n\n### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — verify (2026-03-23T05:45Z)\n\n- **Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\n- **Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running (using `codeharness-shared-*` naming). The `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts. Worked around by using the shared stack directly.\n- **Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path.\n- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find story Status line in the story file — likely looking for `## Status:` pattern that was stripped or mismatched.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — create-story (2026-03-23T05:55Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\n- **File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\n- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)\n\n- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\n- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\n- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — code-review (2026-03-23T06:07Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\n- **LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` — if tarpaulin outputs `\"coverage\": \"85.5\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\n- **LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\n- **Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":26,"oldLines":3,"newStart":26,"newLines":10,"lines":[" - **LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern."," - **Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes."," - **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.","+","+### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — verify (2026-03-23T10:17Z)","+","+- **CLI does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` in JSON output.** `codeharness coverage --json` output includes `tool` but not other `detectCoverageTool()` fields. AC1 and AC2 required supplemental verification by replicating function logic from `dist/index.js`. Documentation/API gap.","+- **AC4 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `parseTestCounts` is internal and not exercised by any CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output. No `codeharness parse-test-output` command.","+- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** No log entries in VictoriaLogs during verification. Expected — container doesn't have Docker-in-Docker so observability stack not running inside it.","+- **Workspace aggregation confirmed.** Bundle shows `parseTestCounts` uses global regex with `matchAll`-style loop for multi-crate workspace test output."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
