 \"currentPhase\": null,\n   293→    \"lastAction\": null,\n   294→    \"acProgress\": null\n   295→  },\n   296→  \"actionItems\": [\n   297→    {\n   298→      \"id\": \"migrated-1\",\n   299→      \"story\": \"8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust\",\n   300→      \"description\": \"**Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\",\n   301→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   302→      \"resolved\": false\n   303→    },\n   304→    {\n   305→      \"id\": \"migrated-2\",\n   306→      \"story\": \"8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust\",\n   307→      \"description\": \"**Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running (using `codeharness-shared-*` naming). The `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts. Worked around by using the shared stack directly.\",\n   308→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   309→      \"resolved\": false\n   310→    },\n   311→    {\n   312→      \"id\": \"migrated-3\",\n   313→      \"story\": \"8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust\",\n   314→      \"description\": \"**Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path.\",\n   315→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   316→      \"resolved\": false\n   317→    },\n   318→    {\n   319→      \"id\": \"migrated-4\",\n   320→      \"story\": \"8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust\",\n   321→      \"description\": \"**Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find story Status line in the story file — likely looking for `## Status:` pattern that was stripped or mismatched.\",\n   322→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   323→      \"resolved\": false\n   324→    },\n   325→    {\n   326→      \"id\": \"migrated-5\",\n   327→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   328→      \"description\": \"**Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\",\n   329→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   330→      \"resolved\": false\n   331→    },\n   332→    {\n   333→      \"id\": \"migrated-6\",\n   334→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   335→      \"description\": \"**File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\",\n   336→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   337→      \"resolved\": false\n   338→    },\n   339→    {\n   340→      \"id\": \"migrated-7\",\n   341→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   342→      \"description\": \"**Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\",\n   343→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   344→      \"resolved\": false\n   345→    },\n   346→    {\n   347→      \"id\": \"migrated-8\",\n   348→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   349→      \"description\": \"**ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\",\n   350→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   351→      \"resolved\": false\n   352→    },\n   353→    {\n   354→      \"id\": \"migrated-9\",\n   355→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   356→      \"description\": \"**Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\",\n   357→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   358→      \"resolved\": false\n   359→    },\n   360→    {\n   361→      \"id\": \"migrated-10\",\n   362→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   363→      \"description\": \"**No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\",\n   364→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   365→      \"resolved\": false\n   366→    },\n   367→    {\n   368→      \"id\": \"migrated-11\",\n   369→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   370→      \"description\": \"**HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\",\n   371→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   372→      \"resolved\": false\n   373→    },\n   374→    {\n   375→      \"id\": \"migrated-12\",\n   376→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   377→      \"description\": \"**LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` — if tarpaulin outputs `\\\"coverage\\\": \\\"85.5\\\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\",\n   378→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   379→      \"resolved\": false\n   380→    },\n   381→    {\n   382→      \"id\": \"migrated-13\",\n   383→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   384→      \"description\": \"**LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\",\n   385→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   386→      \"resolved\": false\n   387→    },\n   388→    {\n   389→      \"id\": \"migrated-14\",\n   390→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   391→      \"description\": \"**Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\",\n   392→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   393→      \"resolved\": false\n   394→    },\n   395→    {\n   396→      \"id\": \"migrated-15\",\n   397→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   398→      \"description\": \"**Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\",\n   399→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   400→      \"resolved\": false\n   401→    }\n   402→  ]\n   403→}\n   404→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01EoBQaME3BVMasq7sgNi6Vg","session_id":"068788d2-fa6f-4c6d-aa64-12d986e1d458","uuid":"87f0c38b-f9c5-4ddd-b90e-56b9ce8292a1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:19:04.989Z"}
